verbose_text: A number of molecules secreted by MSCs have been shown to mediate their immunoregulatory function, including indoleamine-2,3-dioxygenase (IDO), inducible nitric oxide synthase (iNOS), prostaglandin E2 (PGE2), TNF stimulated gene (TSG)-6, and human leukocyte antigen (HLA)-G.
evidence: TNF stimulated gene (TSG)-6, and human leukocyte antigen
